Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.99,0:43:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,which is all that is.\NAnd I could sit there ...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.00,0:43:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,In its linear form.\N... forever. But I'll ask you a few more questions just for the viewers and the listeners.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.76,0:43:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder, too, about entrainment, because quite clearly now as you're speaking, I feel\Nentirely different. There's something that's taking place physically in my heart, and I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.72,0:43:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,going to ask you a question.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.72,0:43:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm in entrainment to, you know, there's something going on that I'm experiencing,\Nas we probably all are. Are there consequences to my leaving the room and going back to my
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.72,0:43:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,little ordinary life?\NNo, because you carry the frequency and the vibration in the imprint. It's like your aura
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.85,0:43:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,imprints it.\NSo it's not like I come down?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.85,0:43:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NGood.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.85,0:44:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it's an availability. So those vibrations, those frequencies, and the knowingness that\Neach one then becomes a part of the aura as an energy field of potentiality. And then
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.26,0:44:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,it comes forth when it's needed.\NDo we all have that?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.50,0:44:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody who's experienced an energy field anywhere in their lifetime of a higher frequency\Ncan pick it up. I don't know. I've never researched that specifically.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.50,0:44:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Would they have to be ...\NWhether you can refuse it or agree to it, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.50,0:44:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Would they have to be over 200?\NWould they have to be over 200 to have a relationship with a higher frequency, or could that happen
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.50,0:44:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,at any level?\NIn other words, despite oneself, one picks it up. Okay, let me just ask that one. It's
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.68,0:44:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,possible that despite oneself, people below 200 pick up on a higher energy field, resist.\NYes, I thought so. See, otherwise there'd be no point. There was a savior, a Buddha,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.71,0:45:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,an avatar.\NSo that frequency is picked up within human consciousness, generally, and it comes down
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.71,0:45:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,through the centuries. And then you don't realize it's within yourself until you reach\Nby agreement. In other words, spirituality doesn't force itself. Nobody's forced through,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.41,0:45:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,see? But then when you're ready for it, it's there because it's in your aura. Yeah.\NVery good.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.64,0:45:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And we even checked one time that the energy field is there because it's in your aura.\NThe energy field of a great teacher can last you through 25 lifetimes, 25 reincarnations.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.86,0:45:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,People don't believe in karma, and they don't have to, and I don't insist that they do.\NBut it will last down through the lifetimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.31,0:45:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,25 lifetimes.\NYeah, at least 25. I didn't ask you if it was more. 25 should do you.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.31,0:45:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I've heard you say that no one calibratable level is better than another, just different\Nfrom each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.31,0:46:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But, you know, in speaking about some of the levels that are under 200, it seems like\Nwouldn't you have to agree some levels are preferable to others?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.31,0:46:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God, yes.\NOkay. Not necessarily better than.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.31,0:46:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we're talking about judgmentalism, you see.\NI know.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.31,0:46:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it better to be a chameleon or a crane? Is it better to be a heron or a hippopotamus?\NYou know, it's not really better than. You know, being a hippo is a hippo, and being
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.66,0:46:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,a whistling crane is something else. You can't really say one is better than the other,\Nprojecting preference. It isn't that it's better than. It's that it is what it is. What
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.19,0:46:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,everything means is what it is. What it is is what it means. What it means is what it\Nis.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.43,0:46:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Clear.\NIdentity and meaning are identical. So if you live in the world of essence, then, you
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.43,0:47:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,see and experience the world differently. And you see that everything is just being\Nthat which it is at that point in its evolution. So what eventually dawns on you is the
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.78,0:47:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,perfection of all things. Each thing is only being what it can be at that moment of its\Nbeing that. So it's an adolescence who's been brainwashed into violence as holiness
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.10,0:47:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,or something. That's all they can believe at that point in this lifetime.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.10,0:47:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And whether this is, this world is not celestial, nor is it hell. It's, what do you call that\Nin between the two?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.44,0:47:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Purgatorial.\NPurgatorial, yes. This world is, to my view, purgatorial.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.44,0:47:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But, for me…\NYou can worry about purgatory some other time. You better worry about it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.44,0:47:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now.\NThis is purgatory. Why? You've got your choice between heaven and hell right here, right
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.44,0:48:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,now.\NBut wouldn't I prefer to hang out in heaven?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.44,0:48:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you prefer to hang out with my kitty cat who might calibrate at 350 as opposed\Nto a Komodo dragon at 40?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.44,0:48:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's because you're spiritually committed, you know. So as a spiritually committed\Nperson, yes, it would be important whether people are of a higher level or a lower level.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.83,0:48:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But the people below, they're looking for sensation and stardom and money and…\NWell, they'll find that if they cuddle up with a Komodo dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.83,0:48:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?\NThey'll find that if they cuddle up with a Komodo dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.83,0:48:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYou know, I'm wondering, I've been to the lectures and the satsangs, and I noticed
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.47,0:48:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that oftentimes people will ask the same questions. Sometimes even the same people will ask the\Nsame questions. And so I'm just curious. Your answers are very consistent. Why can't
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.92,0:49:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,we hear you? Why can't… What's our block from taking the information in?\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.92,0:49:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it may be I didn't articulate it as well as I should have. Plus, I'm aware there's\Nan audience listening. So I'm trying to answer it not only in terms of meaningful to the
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.88,0:49:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,questioner, but so as to answer it in the consciousness of everybody in the audience.\NThey're bringing it up for everyone, you might say, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.88,0:49:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah, and sometimes I'm repetitious because sometimes people are coming up, they present,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.88,0:49:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you know…\NWhat they're really presenting as a psychological, psychiatric problem, you know, social problem
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.88,0:49:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,with their family is really not a spiritual question, you know? And I try to redirect\Nthem that they really should have a counselor that's not really a spiritual. They're
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.91,0:49:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,not really asking the spiritual meaning or aspect of a situation.\NRight. And I've heard you say…
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.00,0:50:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Everything's physical, mental, and spiritual. So some of these disorders that\Npeople bring up…
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.32,0:50:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\N…are not just spiritual. They're also physical and mental, you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.38,0:50:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, definitely.\NYeah, yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.38,0:50:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're trying to direct them in the right way.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.38,0:50:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And also the whole audience is listening as well. Now, I've heard you say at times\Nif someone says, I'm depressed, Dr. Hawkins, and you would say, well, you're not depressed
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.38,0:50:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,enough. Go into the depression more. So I'm just curious, how does one know when they're\Nhitting bottom in a therapeutic way where they can, you know, find something else or
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.60,0:50:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,when they're just juicing, you know, a particular state of mind?\NWell, I don't give that recommendation to everybody willy-nilly.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.60,0:50:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NI'm talking to spiritually-oriented people who are seeing this as a phenomenon that they're
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.60,0:50:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,working through. A person who is just an ordinary person not spiritually committed or in a spiritual\Nlearning system, it might be quite dangerous for them to surrender to a depression and
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.92,0:50:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,commit suicide, you see?\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.96,0:51:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm thinking about as a spiritual, once you join a spiritual evolution, now how you\Nprocess things has different significance. What you're looking to get out of it is the
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.31,0:51:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,meaning and the spiritual growth that's hidden within that situation. For people that are\Nnot safely in that kind of a context, it would be foolish of them to try and fight a depression
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.66,0:51:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,because they'll just end up paralyzed in a hospital, you see?\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.66,0:51:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So I say everything's physical, mental, and spiritual.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.66,0:51:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And you should look at it psychologically, spiritually, and also get help for it within\Nthe physical domain, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.68,0:51:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.68,0:51:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,All levels. Well, speaking of your audience, I'm curious, what is your sense of the best\Nway for your live audience to demonstrate their recognition of the presence of God within
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.55,0:51:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you as their teacher?\NThey do so beautifully by being there.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.77,0:52:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NI think highly of somebody. I go and listen to their lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.77,0:52:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Yeah. They do show up.\NThey do.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.77,0:52:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,They do adore you.\NAnd that I consider the greatest compliment going. You see, it's the fulfillment of my
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.77,0:52:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,obligation to share with the world that which I've known and I know to be of value. And\Ntherefore, they help me fulfill my own potential. So I'm grateful to them for being there.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.77,0:52:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?\NDefinitely.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.57,0:52:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NAnd one of the things I admire in your life that I notice about you is that you spend
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.57,0:52:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot of quiet time in contemplation, meditation with nature, and then you go out there in\Nthe world in a really big way. You work with people as a spiritual teacher, as a doctor,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.57,0:52:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,as a therapist you have. And my question is, how does one navigate these seeming polarities\Nand stay in integrity as you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.57,0:52:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not polarities. They're all potentialities.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.57,0:53:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And this, as I say, like a pipe organ. So with this one, I play the bass notes, and\Nwith this one, I play the high notes. So the overall orientation is to be of service to
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.89,0:53:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the world in whatever way you can be. I went back into practice because there was no other\Npsychiatrist around to see 50 girls there in desperate condition and no doctor. I had
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.89,0:53:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,no intention to go back into practice. And then I found there was a shortage of psychiatrists\Naround here anyway. So I went into part-time practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.89,0:53:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's because there's a need for it within the world. When your own needs are met, then\Nyou try to fulfill the needs of the world. You're trying to complete the fulfillment
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.76,0:53:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,of your own potentiality as an actuality. Each one has a gift. Some people have the\Ngift of benevolence and capacity to comfort others, to look after others, to inspire others.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.91,0:54:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one fulfills their karmic destiny.\NDoes the contemplation and meditation help you to fulfill your own needs so that you're
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.36,0:54:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,able to go out in the world?\NI don't really have any needs about it, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.52,0:54:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Would it help me maybe to fulfill my needs and others to go out in the world and\Nhelp people as you?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.52,0:54:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Those things happen automatically as a consequence of that which you have become. So I believe\Nin meditation and contemplation to be, should be a continuous lifestyle. As we're talking
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.52,0:54:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,now, the meditative part of me is functioning not predominantly because they're not playing\Nthat on the organ. But all the while we're talking, there is that which is reflective
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.56,0:55:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and nonlinear, aware of exactly where we are with it all. It's, you might say, observing.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.57,0:55:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Interpreting, being aware of, interpreting from various levels of consciousness simultaneously.\NSo the awareness is not only of what we're being said in a linear vocal style, but on
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.63,0:55:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,very many dimensions, including beyond this lifetime. All of us here in this room in this\Nmoment are fulfilling our obligation and our capacity. All of us, everyone in this room,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.97,0:55:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,right now.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.10,0:55:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Is fulfilling that potentiality. You see how potentiality is evolving into an actuality\Njust by the sheer presence of us all being together. It's not by accident we're all together.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.26,0:55:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, each one is serving a critical function. Yeah.\NWell, I want to go back to something you did speak briefly of before. I know from your
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.70,0:56:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,writings and your lectures that you emphasize that peace begins within an individual. And\Nthe world is in such a state of distress these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.70,0:56:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And I just wondered if you could speak briefly for the magazine about the individuals that\Nmight be involved with the peace movement today.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.70,0:56:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, don't ask me about peace as a movement and a political, politicalization. Because\NI think it's very provocative and it provokes its opposite. Why? Because it becomes politicized.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.15,0:56:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And as politicized, it becomes wanting to control. And it's, you know, from the viewpoint\Nof the yin-yang of it, it gives you something to oppose, you see. The way to have peace
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.47,0:56:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,is to be peaceful. And people who, this is going to sound ambiguous, but those who declare\Nthey want peace are not telling the truth. Because if you choose peace, you have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.78,0:57:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you have it, why would you be protesting about it? So peace, peace is an interstate.\NWould you say that the peace movement is a waste of time then?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.13,0:57:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd say it's very provocative. It's the opposite.\NAnd how would one access choosing peace?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.64,0:57:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Peace is an inner decision, you see. So how do you bring about peace? Well, people ask\Nthis very often. Through the collective, through the collective. In other words, each person,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.15,0:57:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,by choosing peace within themself, raises the level of consciousness.\NSo the way it's set up in our world is divisive and conflictual. The peace movement against
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.32,0:58:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the war movement. Now, recently we had a peace demonstration, and if you calibrate some of\Nthe leading figures, you'll find that they're all below 200. All of them. All below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.54,0:58:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So how would one, is there a way that one could access that peace within, within the\Npeace movement, without going, without being concerned about the peace movement?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.54,0:58:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so you can't do it by war, war against non-peace.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.60,0:58:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens is, as each person chooses truth rather than falsehood, and integrously moves\Nforward in consciousness, they lift the collective, the collective consciousness of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.23,0:58:49.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Collective, collective, collective consciousness of mankind, then, is like the light of the\Nlevel of the sea. And as you raise the level of the sea, it raises all the ships on the
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.45,0:58:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,sea. What the peace movement tries to do is pick which ships they're going to lift above\Nthe level of the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.80,0:59:05.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NThey're not going to. And therefore, they all, you know, eventually fail. What happens
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.73,0:59:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,is, a society reaches a level of collective awareness, and then because of that which\Nit has become, the peace is in place.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.73,0:59:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The peace is an automatic consequence of the reality of that which they are.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.28,0:59:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to me, most of the peace movements are fakes, and they're just out there, and I get\Nall kinds of solicitations in the slick, slick-looking things in the mail. And when you calibrate
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.56,0:59:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,them, they're below 200.\NRight. Very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.04,0:59:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You're out there to create war in the name of peace.\NThe interview you mentioned about the children that never liked authority growing up, it's
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.04,0:59:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,kind of that same thing.\NYes, they're just opposing anything, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.04,0:59:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NBecause peace would require the resignation of positionalities, and don't you see these
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.04,1:00:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,people value their positionality greater than they do peace? All these people out harassing\Nthe President of the United States, do you think they're bringing about peace? No, they're
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.17,1:00:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,fomenting hatred.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.68,1:00:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, after the Vietnam War, you saw the hatred these movie stars solicit. They're\Nplaying on hatred and pridefulness and everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.97,1:00:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NPridefulness and arrogance, that's not peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.97,1:00:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's what they're bringing into their own life.\NThey get a lot of time in the media, but that's about all. Because the collective consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.64,1:00:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,of mankind reaches a certain degree of wisdom, and out of wisdom it becomes obvious to everybody.\NYou don't have to sell people what's obvious, you see. You don't have to sell them what's
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.89,1:00:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,obvious.\NI would like to ask you about dance.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.91,1:00:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,About what?\NDance.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.91,1:00:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Dance?\NI've seen you dance. I love dance. I've studied dance in my life, and it's a way,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.91,1:01:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess, for me that spirit gets to be inside the physical body. And I've seen you dance.\NI've seen you do the octopus on stage, and I think anyone who's ever seen you dance would
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.97,1:01:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,have to agree, you've really got a special relationship with movement. So I wondered,\Nis that a product of past life experience? Is it a product of your field of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.97,1:01:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,or did you actually get childhood training?\NNo, it was an interest and a talent. And, you know, people, at a certain level of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.26,1:01:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you remember past lives, you see. Maybe we shouldn't talk about such things, because\Na lot of people don't believe in that, see.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.26,1:01:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What level of consciousness?\NOne time I was a temple dancer, and it came to me in one lifetime, one time when I was
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.48,1:02:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,dancing in this lifetime, that whole lifetime, and how I was trained. And in that lifetime\Nas a temple dancer, I see in my mind a design, and I merely act out the design that I already
Dialogue: 0,1:02:03.31,1:02:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,see in my mind. And that's how I was trained. I can see a descending spiral. Now I just\Nbecome the descending spiral. I become.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.79,1:02:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I just become the pattern.\NThat is already within.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.80,1:02:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And you've already.\NYou know, see. That came to me that one time, all of a sudden I remembered that lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.80,1:02:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You're trained into the pattern, and then the body merely conforms to the pattern. And\Nyou can also forget all that, because past life is not something that most people let
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.90,1:02:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,give any credence to.\NWhat level is it, 600 that you remember past lives?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.90,1:02:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, yes, about, yeah, 600.\NWhat were you doing?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.03,1:02:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a recall. It's really a recall.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.03,1:02:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't see it as a past life. Well, yeah, see, I guess you do see it as a past life.\NA different role, a different role. Now, whether that is just something within the collective
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.03,1:03:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that you, because you know, now you identify with the whole collective consciousness, whether\Nyou recall it because you have owned the entire collective consciousness of mankind as one's
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.54,1:03:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,own, or whether it actually happened in a linear chronologic, you see, is irrelevant.\NAll I know is I know what it is to be that dancer, and I know what it is to dance in
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.60,1:03:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,that context of worship of God.\NWhat was the moment that you had that memory? Do you recall what you were doing? You were
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.66,1:03:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,dancing when you had the memory in this current lifetime of this other?\NI was in a state of ecstasy. I was by myself in a state of ecstasy. And then came the recall,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.17,1:04:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,aha, of merely tracing out a pattern. What you're taught is the pattern. And then the\Ndance is merely just the fulfillment of that pattern within. At a certain level, you don't
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.73,1:04:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,dance anymore. You're being danced, and it's effortless. And in that state, you can dance\Nfor hours. I've danced for maybe 24 hours nonstop. No food, no water, nothing. In that
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.66,1:04:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,state of ecstasy, I had to call.\NThat's when I called that ecstasy to a halt, and I realized I had to surrender that to
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.66,1:04:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,God.\NAre there any consequences to dancing that long? When you're in a state of ecstasy, do
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.66,1:04:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you become tired afterward?\NNot that I know of, no. You don't get tired, no, because the energy is continuous. You're
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.92,1:04:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,not depleting anything, because, as I said, I had to let it go. I saw that this, too,\NI must surrender to Thee, O Lord. And that's when I surrendered that.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.68,1:05:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I went into that state of satchitananda, this, too, O Lord. And you weep with joy. If\NI talk about it now, I would break up, so I can't talk about it forever. It brings the
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.02,1:05:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,joy back.\NWell, I'll move on to a different question. The law of attraction, have you heard of it?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.40,1:05:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NIt's this, you know, this big buzz, this secret, the DVD, New Age DVD. Everyone's talking
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.40,1:05:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,about it in the spiritual community.\NThey just discovered it. It's been around forever.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.40,1:05:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no secret, is it?\NBut I wondered...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.40,1:05:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But the hole in mine tends to materialize. I mean, that's an old saw, isn't it?\NNow, is there a correlation between your model for attractor fields and this law of attraction?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:36.40,1:05:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,No. No. Nominally, just the word attractor. In a vague sort of a way, you're attracted\Nto, yes, see, an attractor field, I could use a term from non-linear dynamics. It's
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.83,1:06:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,an energy field, and you're attracted to your own energy field, yes, that with which\Nyou resonate. You're attracted to that which you have become. So once you reach a certain
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.40,1:06:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,level, you prefer a rural, easygoing lifestyle with nature and an emphasis on beauty and\Naesthetics, and you're not interested in the law of attraction.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.92,1:06:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.\NAnd you're attracted to the world and accomplishment and all that.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.92,1:06:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I would wonder that even if the intention, if your intention isn't from a good place,\Nif your attention's from a lower level of consciousness, isn't there a danger that what
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.36,1:06:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you're intending to bring into your life with this law of attraction could also be sourced\Nfrom a lower motivation?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.36,1:06:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's not go out there. Let's just take the law of attraction. First of all, it's not\Nlaw. It's just observation.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.96,1:06:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NWhat you hold in mind tends to materialize.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.96,1:07:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You tend to bring it into your life because you're holding the pattern of it, and naturally,\Nyou're identifying with that pattern. That which you hold in mind tends to materialize.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.31,1:07:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Every place I've lived for 50 years, each place arose as a consequence of holding, envisioning\Nthat which I would appreciate the most.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.31,1:07:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.\NAnd not through searching.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.56,1:07:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I would just picture a little house near the creek someplace and the woods all around,\Nand next thing I know, somebody called me and said, you know, the place next door is
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.46,1:07:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,for sale, and you're the only one I want living next to me.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.46,1:07:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And back east, the same thing happened. I pictured woods and the beautiful things,\Nand sure enough, it turned out 25 acres of woods and an elegant lifestyle, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.78,1:07:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So whatever you hold in mind tends to materialize.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.78,1:08:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, there's a lot of people holding in mind Cadillacs and mansions, so I'm wondering,\Nwouldn't that be the source motivation of what you want?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.78,1:08:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, for you, nature brings contemplation and quiet and a sweet space.\NYeah, I'm just wondering about the source motivation.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:16.36,1:08:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you've already answered it.\NWanting it tends to keep it away.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.36,1:08:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't picture wanting a Cadillac.\NYou picture yourself having a Cadillac and being in a Cadillac
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.36,1:08:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and being joyful in it and appreciating it.\NSo I have a beautiful Cadillac.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.93,1:08:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It already worked.\NIt's an 84, and it's been restored, and I love it.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.93,1:08:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So somebody says, wouldn't you rather have a new one?\NFrankly, no, because I know where everything is.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.93,1:08:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I can drive the 84 Caddy without even thinking.\NIf I got into a new Cadillac, I'd have to go to school for a month with all the dials and gadgets
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.93,1:09:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and it would be distressing.\NIn fact, we have a new car in the family, and I don't know how to drive it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.93,1:09:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so complicated.\NI don't know how in the world they'd even make it work.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.51,1:09:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me ask you a question about if I did my math right, you're going to be 80 this year,\Nso maybe I can be the first to wish you a happy birthday in a few months.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.51,1:09:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulations.\NI am wondering, as you grow older, have you gotten any provisions or structure together
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.51,1:09:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,to ensure the legacy of your teaching?\NThe legacy of your teachings before you leave us in form, which none of us want to be soon.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.51,1:09:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I've tried to provide everything in written form, verbal form, audio form,\Nin all the possible formats that facilitate teaching,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:45.89,1:10:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and we've created a nonprofit 501c3 Institute of Spiritual Studies that goes on into perpetuity.\NAnd the responsibility of the Institute for Spiritual Studies is to continue on,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.52,1:10:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,make sure that the materials become available, stay available into perpetuity.\NBeautiful.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.52,1:10:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason is, for instance, I'm not too verbal this morning.\NWhat do you call it, Wang Ho?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.98,1:10:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't even think anymore.\NAnyway, many of the most valuable teachings,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.27,1:10:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,or from 800, 900 years ago, or something like that,\Nsome teacher that lived in India 900 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.27,1:10:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and it was recorded, and we're still reading it today.\NSo very good, we'll be able to still...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:47.74,1:10:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So whatever the essence of the truth of it,\Nto make sure that it's available.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.74,1:11:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What's valuable about the work I do, I think,\Nis that I've bulwarked an obvious statement.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.74,1:11:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're in a high state, you can read something,\Nlike the Great Sage said 1,000 years ago, and it's obvious.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.77,1:11:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you're not in a great state,\Nit requires a great deal of bulwarking and explanation.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.77,1:11:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So to me, what's missing is the explanation.\NNow, a lot of the great teachings of ancient time was nonverbal.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:23.00,1:11:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So the difficulty with a book, or even the verbal translation,\Nespecially in Buddhism and Hinduism,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.73,1:11:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a lot of misconception of what was meant\Nby what the teacher said.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:35.73,1:11:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason is because when it was said,\Nit was said, first of all, in a certain context.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.96,1:11:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Secondly, it was said with certain gestures,\Nwith certain emphasis,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.15,1:11:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,with certain physical expressions.\NAnd the meaning is conveyed in the totality.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:54.50,1:12:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And out of the totality, they extract a linear verbalization.\NIt's a wonder that anybody gets what was meant by that,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:03.17,1:12:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,because...\NTrue.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.17,1:12:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, even when I'm, you know, having a lecture,\NI can tell by one gesture and the way I'm holding my hand,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.17,1:12:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,they got what that is.\NNow, how would a translator put that into a verbalization?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.17,1:12:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,At the point where he says,\Nhappened of its own.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.30,1:12:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, you get it nonverbally.\NYou obviously saw it happened of its own.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:28.30,1:12:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no...\NI don't say to your thing about,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.30,1:12:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,gee, I think I'll do something clever in the middle of our talk\Nand it'll be unusual or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.30,1:12:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It just happens spontaneously.\NSo the emergence of reality is spontaneous, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.30,1:12:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And so what's lost in the translations\Nis what they meant by that.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.38,1:12:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I noticed as we started up that you and Susan had this look,\Nand I thought, you have such a symbiotic relationship.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.38,1:13:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So I wanted to ask, when and where did you first meet?\NAnd, you know, was it love at first sight?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.38,1:13:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We first met in a dancing class.\NOh, there you go, the dance comes back.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.38,1:13:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, and the recognition was instantaneous.\NI looked across the room and I felt this incredible surge of energy shoot
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.38,1:13:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,between the two of us, and it just knocked me out.\NAnd I thought, that's it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.38,1:13:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,All nonverbal, nothing.\NIt was just like a sudden knowingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.38,1:13:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's very sweet to witness the support and the caring.\NAnd you're currently working on a new book.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:37.38,1:13:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You referenced that earlier.\NI'm working on four books right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:40.38,1:13:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.\NI always work on a few at a time.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.38,1:13:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,My goodness.\NDo you have any?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.38,1:13:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm working on, let's see, three, four, about four books, yeah.\NDo you have a little sneak preview for us, or is there any synchronized?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:53.38,1:14:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm working on one called Spiritual Reality in Modern Man.\NAnd then we're working on a book of charts, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.69,1:14:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,all the lecture charts that we put out, about 105 of those.\NSo each one, I picture a chart on one side and a page of explanation on the other.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.82,1:14:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a rapid recapitulation through the content of the course.\NAnd then I'm working, we're working on a dictionary of calibrations,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.08,1:14:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and we've done thousands of them.\NSo we're constantly calibrating everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:27.08,1:14:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I make, I jot them all down,\Nand someday I'll get myself collected to bring them up to date.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.52,1:14:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there's the book.\NI did lectures years ago on healing, self-healing and healing.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:41.52,1:14:47.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And those are being put in book form.\NSo right now I'm correcting the manuscript to the book form
Dialogue: 0,1:14:47.97,1:14:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,because it was given verbally and very informally.\NAnd now in book form, you have to change the languaging.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.97,1:14:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, what you say spontaneously to an audience,\Nyou can't just forbid and put it down necessarily.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:59.97,1:15:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NYou have to translate it more into what people are used to in reading, see.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.32,1:15:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're working on those four.\NAnd then in my spare time, I have to write,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:13.73,1:15:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm always preparing something for the next lecture.\NNow the next lecture is God versus science, I think, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.05,1:15:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So I had to put together, you know, when we check all these things out,\Nthen I make a list of them so they will come,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:32.72,1:15:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the information will come out in the next lecture.\NSo there's also, besides the four books,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:37.82,1:15:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,constantly preparing slides for the next lecture.\NRight now, right now, environmentalism is, you know, very big.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.17,1:15:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NYou see, the minute you put an ism on a thing,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.17,1:15:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,it becomes a politicized power play.\NAnd all the politics and game playing, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:57.43,1:16:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is environmental, you know, environmental warming\Nand environmental pollution, oh, global warming.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:05.84,1:16:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Global warming.\NAnd there's global warming.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:09.84,1:16:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there's environmental pollution.\NThe mistake is to put them together as causal
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.50,1:16:28.27,Default,,0,0,0,,because global warming is independent of environmentalism.\NMan's input into the environment doesn't affect the temperature
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.27,1:16:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,on Earth more than 0.8 degrees Fahrenheit.\NSo pollution is one thing, and it has detrimental effects.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:38.26,1:16:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Earth warming is due to the magnetic activity of the surface of the sun.\NAnd is independent of man.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.91,1:17:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The global temperature fluctuates over the many centuries.\NThat was found by core drillings at the,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.55,1:17:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,ice drillings at the polar, at the poles.\NYou can get the temperature back over 10,000 years.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:11.55,1:17:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And it is concordant.\NAnd so the next lecture,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:16.64,1:17:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,which is next Saturday or a week from tomorrow or whatever,\NI'll give the scientific references, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.06,1:17:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we do, see, when we do consciousness research,\Nwe come out with the truth of the thing,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:31.28,1:17:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,irrespective of what mankind believes.\NSo when we find the disparity,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.44,1:17:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I've discovered over the years, we're always right.\NIf her arm goes weak when I say
Dialogue: 0,1:17:44.82,1:17:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,temperature change on the Earth is due to man\Nand her arm goes weak,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:49.75,1:17:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,she's always right.\NI mean, that arm is always right.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:52.75,1:17:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So I believed it too.\NI thought, well, you know, it's probably man's activities.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:57.75,1:17:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe that too.\NSo we got to know.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:59.75,1:18:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, hey, what is that?\NSo then I began to research it.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:02.75,1:18:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And I finally know that the explanation is independent of man's existence.\NMan contributes to 0.8 degrees Fahrenheit.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.84,1:18:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So pollution is a problem of its own.\NNow, what is the cause of pollution?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.48,1:18:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you the secret of that.\NOverpopulation.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.80,1:18:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NYou can't live as a human being without creating problems.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.80,1:18:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to eat.\NThat's going to create garbage, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.80,1:18:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to go to the bathroom.\NYou've got to have sewage.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.80,1:18:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So environmentalism, environmental damage,\Nis due to just the sheer population.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:43.12,1:18:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That would be good for people to hear\Nbecause that's not the popular belief.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.56,1:18:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, overpopulation is the cause of pollution.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:52.56,1:18:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And earth temperature is due to the effect of the sun.\NAnd man's not going to do anything about that.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:59.56,1:19:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a little bigger.\NMan's not going to affect the temperature on the earth.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:04.17,1:19:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So all you can control is pollution.\NThe only way you can control pollution is stop having so many children.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.42,1:19:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'll be doing my part to help you there.\NWell, the Western world is already doing that.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.42,1:19:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The birth rate has fallen precipitously in Europe,\Nfalling in the United States.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:21.84,1:19:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,In civilized countries, Western world,\Nthe birth rate is declining rapidly.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:27.84,1:19:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,There's some books out now about it.\NI forget the name of the book.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:30.93,1:19:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But America Alone, I think, is the name of the book.\NThat if the birth rate continues as it is,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:36.93,1:19:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,as it is already doing in Scandinavia especially,\Nthe birth rate is so low that every civilization ceases
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.93,1:19:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,when it no longer can repopulate itself.\NIn our Western society,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.12,1:19:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the population is declining at a rapid rate.\NPeople are putting off having children.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:56.44,1:20:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They're viewing it as an optional lifestyle.\NIn traditional America, there was no question about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.48,1:20:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody got married and had kids.\NSure.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.48,1:20:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody thought,\Ngee, should I stay single and childless my whole life?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:10.48,1:20:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't remember a single person contemplating that.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.48,1:20:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Except people who joined nunneries.\NRight. But it is a choice we have today.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.48,1:20:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, other than religious people.\NNobody thought,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:20.48,1:20:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,it wasn't an option.\NI think I'll stay single my whole life
Dialogue: 0,1:20:23.48,1:20:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and never have any kids.\NI don't remember even thinking about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.48,1:20:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It was just presumed.\NYou would get married, have children,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.48,1:20:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and have a job,\Nand support your wife and children,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:32.48,1:20:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and that was pretty much the way it is.\NThen you retire at 65 and you get a watch.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.48,1:20:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you hire an RV,\Nand you have a, what do you call those things
Dialogue: 0,1:20:42.28,1:20:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,where you drive around the country?\NOh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.28,1:20:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You're 65, you retire, see?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:48.28,1:20:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And you either rent or own a...\NMotorhome.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:51.28,1:20:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you call it?\NThe RV, motorhome.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:53.28,1:20:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Motorhome, yeah.\NThen you explore the U.S. for a year.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:57.37,1:21:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you come home\Nand you have your heart attack and die.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.37,1:21:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly.\NAnd then your wife goes and lives with the grandchildren
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.37,1:21:07.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and becomes granny\Nso that the mother of the children can go to work.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:07.37,1:21:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So it all worked out very neatly,\Nand that's the way you presume life would be, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.66,1:21:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Perfect.\NWell, I want to thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.66,1:21:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I really, I have many more questions,\Nbut I also want to...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:19.66,1:21:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, thank you so much.\NThank you for your precious time, so...
Dialogue: 0,1:21:22.66,1:21:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, well, it was enjoyable.\NYeah, for me as well,
Dialogue: 0,1:21:25.66,1:21:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,just to be with you here today.\NThank you, Dr. Hawkins.
